Set Directory ACL
Parameters:

dirID: The specific directory ID
aclsString: the acl description string, the syntax as following:
[Inherit]|[-Inherit]|<[-][G|U][Group/User ID]{:[+|-|*][ACTION][,[+|-|*][ACTION]]*}>|<[-][G|U][Group/User ID]{:[+|-|*][ACTION][,[+|-|*][ACTION]]*}>|...
Inherit means to set the access control of the selected directory inherit from the parent
- before user or group ID means remove the user from the Access control list.
+ stand allow. - stand for denied, * stand for don't care
[ACTION] are the action, can be one of the value [All|ACL|Create|Read|Delete|Update|Browse|NewDoc|DeleteDoc|UpdateDoc]
e.g G19230:*ACL,+Create|-U19234|G19242:+ACL,+Create+Delete+Read|U19243:-All Inherit
